author: @josephprovencher6345
content: @@summerstar143 Ty so VERY MUCH! It was definitely worth the wait after all of these years. She did some amazing classics but I gotta admit that I was just a little bummed that she did an acoustic version of Express Yourself, BUT at least she did it lol. Omg, experiencing Rain live which she hasn't done since The Girlie Show Tour in 1993 or 1994 was ABSOLUTELY amazing. Also Live To Tell was so sad yet beautiful all wrapped into one, I have to admit that I cried during it. I actually cried during a couple songs to be honest. Music is definitely good for the heart and soul.
